<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="345" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[852,1558,138,1472]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">
Basal leaves oblong, subobtuse, the cauline lanceolate, acute
<emphasis box="[916,920,526,549]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">.</emphasis>
Outer perianth-segments 6-8 mm, oblong-ovate, green or yellowish, often brown-striate, glabrous, the lateral patent, the median erect, cucullate; inner as long as the outer, ovate to lanceolate, dark purple, rarely greenish, densely hairy
<emphasis box="[1435,1439,609,632]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">.</emphasis>
Labellum up to 13 x 15 mm, dark purple, villous with coloured hairs at margin, deeply 3-lobed, not globose-inflated; lateral lobes patent, obtuse, yellowish in the centre and with darker lines; middle lobe often slightly emarginate, with revolute margin, rarely convex; 
<emphasis box="[856,957,747,770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">speculum</emphasis>
large, shiny, blue, yellow at margin, sometimes 3-lobed
<emphasis box="[1550,1554,747,770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">.</emphasis>
Connective obtuse
<emphasis box="[1058,1062,775,798]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">.</emphasis>
2n = 36
<emphasis box="[1157,1161,775,798]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
